For the skate with nut-brown butter, season the skate on both sides with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Heat the butter with the oil in a frying pan and cook the skate for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until almost cooked through.Add the capers, lemon juice and olives and warm through.For the tomato and herb salad, place all of the salad ingredients into a bowl and mix well.To serve, place the skate onto a plate, drizzle over the nut-brown butter and place the salad alongside.